@startuml IncidentFlowStateMachine
title IncidentFlow - State Machine Diagram

[*] --> OPEN

OPEN --> TRIAGED : triage()
OPEN --> CANCELLED : cancel()
OPEN --> ESCALATED : escalate()

TRIAGED --> ASSIGNED : assign(responsable)
TRIAGED --> CANCELLED : cancel()
TRIAGED --> ESCALATED : escalate()

ASSIGNED --> IN_PROGRESS : start_work()
ASSIGNED --> CANCELLED : cancel()
ASSIGNED --> ESCALATED : escalate()

IN_PROGRESS --> RESOLVED : resolve(summary)
IN_PROGRESS --> ESCALATED : escalate()

RESOLVED --> CLOSED : close()\n(CRITICAL must have summary)
RESOLVED --> IN_PROGRESS : reopen()\n(if not from CLOSED)

ESCALATED --> ASSIGNED : reasign_and_continue()
ESCALATED --> IN_PROGRESS : continue_work()

CANCELLED --> [*]
CLOSED --> [*]

note right of OPEN
  Estado inicial cuando se reporta
  un incidente
end note

note right of CRITICAL
  Requiere notificación inmediata
  No puede cerrarse sin resumen
  Debe tener responsable asignado
end note

note right of CLOSED
  Final - no vuelve a IN_PROGRESS
  AuditLog registrado
  Timeline completado
end note

@enduml
